{2000}{}{ These records I leave for my descendants as a}  
{2001}{}{ warning. Keep them secret from the other inhabitants}  
{2002}{}{ and pass them from father to son, as my father did to}  
{2003}{}{ me.}  
{2004}{}{}  
{2005}{}{ Our people's history begins in Vault 27. This massive}  
{2006}{}{ underground bunker was built before the Great War,}  
{2007}{}{ and is located near Phoenix, Arizona.}  
{2008}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2009}{}{ To you, my descendants, such a place might seem}  
{2010}{}{ unwelcoming and strange. You are used to the sunlight}  
{2011}{}{ and the golden sands of Sonora; you cannot}  
{2012}{}{ understand the gloomy rooms of the Vault with its low}  
{2013}{}{ ceilings and cold steel walls. But those very walls and}  
{2014}{}{ technology saved our lives and our ancestors' lives,}  
{2015}{}{ when nuclear bombs fell on the earth.}  
{2016}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2017}{}{ For a long time, we didn't dare to go to the surface.}  
{2018}{}{ The world above was uninhabitable due to mutants,}  
{2019}{}{ ruins, and high radiation. But the longer the}  
{2020}{}{ scientists and citizens argued about it, the fewer}  
{2021}{}{ resources remained in the Vault for survival. Society}  
{2022}{}{ was fracturing, riots broke out one after another,}  
{2023}{}{ and some residents left for the wasteland on their}  
{2024}{}{ own. A decision had to be made quickly. The only thing}  
{2025}{}{ that could ensure our survival was the Garden of Eden}  
{2026}{}{ Creation Kit. A great pre-war technology capable of}  
{2027}{}{ breathing life into the desert. Scientists agreed that}  
{2028}{}{ using it near the Vault would be a reckless waste of}  
{2029}{}{ this valuable technology. The positive effect would be}  
{2030}{}{ nullified by the environment. And we couldn't explore}  
{2031}{}{ distant lands.}  
{2032}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2033}{}{ When the situation became desperate, I gathered the}  
{2034}{}{ best people I could trust even a little. We stole the}  
{2035}{}{ G.E.C.K. and left the Vault, leaving most of the}  
{2036}{}{ population to fend for themselves. The journey was}  
{2037}{}{ tough. Many died from radiation, mutants, and}  
{2038}{}{ occasional raiders. Some betrayed us and were}  
{2039}{}{ executed. At the end of the journey, only a few}  
{2040}{}{ families remained. When hope was lost, we stumbled}  
{2041}{}{ upon this unremarkable place. The G.E.C.K. detector}  
{2042}{}{ deemed it suitable for creating a garden city. But}  
{2043}{}{ even with this technology, it took years before we}  
{2044}{}{ managed to establish the Villa.}  
{2045}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2046}{}{ Now you know the price of our prosperity. And}  
{2047}{}{ although I do not regret what happened, doubts}  
{2048}{}{ remain deep in my soul. Did we do the right thing? How}  
{2049}{}{ many people did we betray? How many did we doom to}  
{2050}{}{ suffering after our departure? No one can answer}  
{2051}{}{ these questions now. So the only right decision is to}  
{2052}{}{ forget the past and live for the future.}  
{2053}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2054}{}{ Our future is our land and our children. Protect them.}  
{2055}{}{ Preserve our way. Avoid ancient technologies. Drive}  
{2056}{}{ away outsiders before they can cause harm. If one}  
{2057}{}{ generation breaks the covenant, the community will}  
{2058}{}{ fall.}  
{2059}{}{**END-PAR**}  
{2060}{}{ Just as Vault 27 once fell.}  
{2061}{}{**END-DISK**}



