# - SETTLEMENT
{3000}{}{ - October 23, 2077:}
{3001}{}{ Starting this diary on the advice of the}
{3002}{}{ psychologist. My family and I were at home doing our}
{3003}{}{ usual activities when suddenly the siren blared over}
{3004}{}{ Mesa. Catherine thought it was a routine system}
{3005}{}{ check. Still, I insisted we take shelter in the vault.}
{3006}{}{ On the way, the radio reported the first explosions}
{3007}{}{ on the West Coast. Soon after, we saw a flash over}
{3008}{}{ Phoenix. The sound of the explosion reached us later.}
{3009}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3010}{}{ Moving in was hell. There was a jam before the vault,}
{3011}{}{ we had to abandon the car on the road. We were}
{3012}{}{ assigned a room and given one Pip-Boy for the whole}
{3013}{}{ family. They also put Mexicans in our room! Turns out,}
{3014}{}{ there are way more people in the vault than there}
{3015}{}{ should be. We were lucky - some are sleeping in the}
{3016}{}{ corridors. What were the Vault-Tec clerks thinking}
{3017}{}{ when they made the settlement lists?}
{3018}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3019}{}{ - November 12, 2077:}
{3020}{}{ My neighbors and I couldn't get along for a long time.}
{3021}{}{ We divided the room with a screen into two parts.}
{3022}{}{ Catherine demanded that I evict them. But what can I}
{3023}{}{ do in such a situation? The children reconciled us. For}
{3024}{}{ their sake, we agreed to behave decently. After all,}
{3025}{}{ little Susie has the hardest time of all. And the}
{3026}{}{ overseer can't cope with overpopulation. Information}
{3027}{}{ about illegal settlers turned out to be false. It looks}
{3028}{}{ like Vault-Tec is in for some serious lawsuits. But}
{3029}{}{ what should we do now?}
{3030}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3031}{}{ - February 7, 2078:}
{3032}{}{ My Mexican neighbor was killed, suspicions fell on me, of}
{3033}{}{ course. I spent a day in a punishment cell. The killer}
{3034}{}{ turned out to be a former truck driver - typical}
{3035}{}{ criminal, mentally ill. He finally went crazy and claimed}
{3036}{}{ that the vault was overpopulated with illegal Mexicans.}
{3037}{}{ But something else is more important. I used to want}
{3038}{}{ the neighbors to disappear. And now I feel like I've lost}
{3039}{}{ a family member. And by the way, only 15% of the}
{3040}{}{ population is Mexican. Their eviction will not solve the}
{3041}{}{ problem permanently.}
{3042}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3043}{}{ - December 11, 2082:}
{3044}{}{ Water and electricity supplies have been cut. The}
{3045}{}{ education and entertainment sections are closed. Food}
{3046}{}{ rations are given out on schedule, one per person.}
{3047}{}{ More deaths, and there are fights in the corridors.}
{3048}{}{ The medical office is overwhelmed. Constant stress.}
{3049}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3050}{}{ - January 2, 2083:}
{3051}{}{ Another murder, this time a white American. Zachary}
{3052}{}{ Taylor, a former soldier and Anchorage veteran, took}
{3053}{}{ charge of the investigation. He quickly found the}
{3054}{}{ "culprit" and, along with his followers, carried out a}
{3055}{}{ lynching. I had to go along with it to avoid suspicion,}
{3056}{}{ but I stood in the column of dissenters. I need to be}
{3057}{}{ more cautious and take a neutral, waiting position. I}
{3058}{}{ initially sympathized with Taylor, but when he}
{3059}{}{ suggested expelling all Mexicans outside, I got}
{3060}{}{ seriously worried. I wouldn't want to see such a person}
{3061}{}{ as overseer.}
{3062}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3063}{}{ - March 13, 2084:}
{3064}{}{ Hugo and his gang seized the water purification}
{3065}{}{ section and started blackmailing the overseer.}
{3066}{}{ Taylor's men took action. The two factions}
{3067}{}{ slaughtered each other in the cramped spaces. It}
{3068}{}{ ended with the lynching of all the defeated, as well as}
{3069}{}{ their accomplices and the station workers. Well. We fled}
{3070}{}{ to the vault to escape war. But war awaited us here.}
{3071}{}{ Maybe it's in people's blood. Susie cries at night when}
{3072}{}{ she dreams of our home. Can't wait to get to the}
{3073}{}{ surface.}
{3074}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3075}{}{ - December 16, 2084:}
{3076}{}{ This is the end. The overseer cut all the supplies.}
{3077}{}{ Taylor's men killed him in his sleep and forcefully took}
{3078}{}{ his position. Now Zachary Taylor is our new overseer.}
{3079}{}{ And I dread to think what rules this old soldier will}
{3080}{}{ establish here. Twenty people disappeared from the}
{3081}{}{ vault overnight. No one saw anything. No one knows}
{3082}{}{ anything. And under no circumstances should you ask}
{3083}{}{ about it.}
{3084}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3085}{}{ - August 24, 2091:}
{3086}{}{ Thanks to Taylor's dictatorship, order and discipline}
{3087}{}{ have reigned in the vault all this time. It was hard, but}
{3088}{}{ we managed. There are rumors of going to the surface.}
{3089}{}{ This thought is incredibly welcome, especially for Susie.}
{3090}{}{ But the overseer made it clear that it's too early. If}
{3091}{}{ you think about it, much has changed: a new}
{3092}{}{ generation has grown up, and we have grown old and}
{3093}{}{ gotten used to these cold walls. Most are afraid to}
{3094}{}{ leave. And where would we go? My house is probably}
{3095}{}{ burned down or crumbled to dust. And what about}
{3096}{}{ here? We lack food, water, air, and the blue sky}
{3097}{}{ overhead. We need time to gather our thoughts.}
{3098}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3099}{}{ - January 18, 2092:}
{3100}{}{ There are more and more heated debates about}
{3101}{}{ leaving. Reconnaissance results are disappointing.}
{3102}{}{ Some believe that the G.E.C.K. will change the}
{3103}{}{ situation, others think its effect will be muted by the}
{3104}{}{ environment. Society is splitting into factions again,}
{3105}{}{ just like it did before. But the overseer is not the}
{3106}{}{ same - he's old and weak. The strength has faded from}
{3107}{}{ his face. Or maybe it's the dim light illuminating his}
{3108}{}{ tired gaze. Will we really grow old in this crypt? Some}
{3109}{}{ have left the vault. Taylor told them not to return.}
{3110}{}{ And Susie was with them. I am pathetic.}
{3111}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3112}{}{ - March 22, 2092:}
{3113}{}{ Felix Tejada did it. He fought his way to the G.E.C.K.}
{3114}{}{ and led his followers into the wasteland. He had been}
{3115}{}{ preparing for this plan for several years. I also}
{3116}{}{ received an invitation from him, but I declined. After}
{3117}{}{ all, Katherine wouldn't go, and she is the only thing I}
{3118}{}{ have left. And I simply don't want to. The overseer has}
{3119}{}{ sealed the vault door for good. Ironically, he used to}
{3120}{}{ want to expel as many people as possible, but now he}
{3121}{}{ won't let anyone out.}
{3122}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3123}{}{ Now the vault is empty. And quiet.}
{3124}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3125}{}{ Like a crypt.}
{3126}{}{**END-PAR**}
{3127}{}{ That's fine. Let it stay that way.}
{3128}{}{**END-DISK**}



